1
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:11,420
Is the reason why you've decorated my room like this because you like this style?

2
00:00:11,420 --> 00:00:12,780
Yeah, I like it.

3
00:00:12,780 --> 00:00:15,380
I've never known how he spends his days.

4
00:00:15,420 --> 00:00:20,580
I've never thought a small club that I built with my own two hands would catch a capitalist's eye like you.

5
00:00:20,580 --> 00:00:22,340
You should consider it.

6
00:00:22,340 --> 00:00:23,860
I can handle his naughtiness.

7
00:00:23,860 --> 00:00:25,180
I can deal with him even if he's worse than this.

8
00:00:25,180 --> 00:00:27,540
That's enough. Stop it, guys!

9
00:00:27,540 --> 00:00:29,580
Do you think it's cool to tease your friend like this?

10
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:39,200
Let's go, Kuea.

11
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:42,759
It's fine.

12
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:43,960
Thanks.

13
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:45,640
But I'm okay.

14
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:48,160
Hey, you guys.

15
00:01:49,479 --> 00:01:50,479
Let's go to class.

16
00:01:50,840 --> 00:01:51,560
We'll be late.

17
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:52,840
Let's go.

18
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:06,320
So what are we going to do?

19
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:08,199
Who's going to be in my group?

20
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:15,640
Nuer, you'll be in my group too, right?

21
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:19,320
Up to Kuea.

22
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:22,520
If he's okay with that, I'll join.

23
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:23,680
He can't!

24
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:26,280
There's always five of us in the group.

25
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:28,240
We've never had any problems.

26
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:32,640
Why are you acting like a kid splitting their football teams?

27
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:35,800
Actually, Nuer doesn't even want to be in our group.

28
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:37,480
The professor forced him to be here.

29
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:38,920
Isn't that right, Syn?

30
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:40,480
"Nanajitang," to each his own.

31
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:42,600
I wouldn't know.

32
00:02:45,720 --> 00:02:48,480
But Nuer was a computer engineering student.

33
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:49,920
He's also the top of the class.

34
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:53,640
I think this formula one project needs his godlike skill.

35
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:56,920
You're right.

36
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,560
We can't, Jab!

37
00:02:58,560 --> 00:03:00,240
There're always just the five of us!

38
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:02,360
Each hand has five fingers. Have you seen anyone with six fingers?

39
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:04,880
- One. Two. Three. Four. Five.
- Will you shut up?

40
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:07,520
What the hell is wrong with you guys?

41
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:09,880
This is such a waste of time. I'm going to another group.

42
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,320
Hey! Wait!

43
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:22,160
Calm down and drink YenYen first.

44
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:23,360
Please.

45
00:03:23,480 --> 00:03:26,600
We're about to sort out this issue.

46
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:28,120
Right, Kuea?

47
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:30,560
Please stay calm and sit down.

48
00:03:31,140 --> 00:03:32,120
Please.

49
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:37,520
Let's finalize this already.

50
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:39,200
If Kuea lets me,

51
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:40,760
I'll be in this group.

52
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:42,760
But if Kuea doesn't want me to,

53
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,360
I can go to another group.

54
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:47,480
There's just Kuea in this group for him, huh.

55
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:51,480
Fine.

56
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,200
So there's me,

57
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:54,360
Nuchy,

58
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,040
Ton,

59
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:55,600
Jab,

60
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:56,320
Syn,

61
00:03:56,320 --> 00:03:58,320
and Nuer.

62
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:00,280
Six of us.

63
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:01,800
Okay?

64
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:03,720
Thank you.

65
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:06,120
Let me know if you need any help.

66
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:10,320
Kuea.

67
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:13,320
Can I talk to you for a bit?

68
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,200
About what?

69
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:17,560
About what happened this morning.

70
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:20,959
It's okay. I know that you didn't mean to tease me like that.

71
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:23,560
But the other two.

72
00:04:24,860 --> 00:04:26,520
Does he mean you and me?

73
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:27,640
I think so.

74
00:04:27,760 --> 00:04:29,200
He's staring at us.

75
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:35,880
If you feel like there's an evil ghost following you around,

76
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:39,520
I can take you to the monk so he can sprinkle you with holy water to get rid of the bad fortune.

77
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:16,080
Hia...

78
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:18,080
You can do it!

79
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:20,800
What's that?

80
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,720
Over there, see?

81
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:25,560
Where?

82
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:28,560
You can do it!

83
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:53,340
What's wrong, Foei?

84
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:54,400
I see that Hia--

85
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:55,440
I mean...

86
00:05:56,280 --> 00:06:00,240
I see that Mr. Lian is happy, so I'm happy too.

87
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,120
Here.

88
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:05,800
The document from the legal department.

89
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:07,480
About buying the Keerati Mansion.

90
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:09,120
I've sorted everything out for you.

91
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,800
Oh, put it down.

92
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:25,120
Everything's done.

93
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:26,960
You want me to get out, don't you?

94
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:27,840
Alright, sir.

95
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:34,320
You're not scolding me yet.

96
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:35,680
You're in a good mood, right?

97
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:37,240
Foei.

98
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:39,640
You're going to scold me soon.

99
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:41,000
I got it, sir.

100
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:11,040
Try moving this one here.

101
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:12,760
This one?

102
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:14,080
Yeah.

103
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,280
Okay.

104
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,640
Move it over here?

105
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:17,280
Yes.

106
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:24,240
Syn!

107
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:26,240
Can you bring me a pen?

108
00:07:40,159 --> 00:07:41,240
Sorry.

109
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:42,640
I just went to the lavatory.

110
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:48,440
Nuer.

111
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:50,480
You're Nuchy's partner, aren't you?

112
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:51,920
Why don't you go and help her?

113
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:54,159
I saw that no one was helping Kuea.

114
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:56,200
I only came here to give him a pen.

115
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:57,640
Gosh!

116
00:07:58,320 --> 00:07:59,680
Come check this first.

117
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:04,400
Ton, Jab!

118
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:06,200
What?

119
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:07,560
What's wrong?

120
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:11,360
It's like this again.

121
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:12,840
It's frozen?

122
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:14,720
Yeah.

123
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:18,960
I think we should clearly define our roles and responsibilities for this project.

124
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:21,200
I agree.

125
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:23,360
Right now, we're working in pairs.

126
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:27,720
So there's Kuea and I, Ton and Jab, Nuchy and Nuer.

127
00:08:28,520 --> 00:08:31,480
Kuea and I will be responsible for the engine part.

128
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:34,120
Ton and Jab will be responsible for the external part.

129
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:37,520
As for Nuchy and Nuer,

130
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:40,880
you guys can be responsible for the research and data collection part.

131
00:08:41,640 --> 00:08:45,120
I think we all should help with the research and data collection.

132
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:46,200
Let's just do what he said.

133
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:48,680
There are two geniuses in our group.

134
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:50,680
We should make use of them.

135
00:08:50,920 --> 00:08:54,040
Syn, you're a visionary leader.

136
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,200
You're amazing.

137
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:58,160
But...

138
00:08:58,160 --> 00:08:59,240
It's okay, Kuea.

139
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:01,680
I'm not good at the engine stuff anyway.

140
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:04,800
Let's follow Syn's suggestions for now.

141
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:08,080
We can make adjustments later.

142
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:10,080
Okay.

143
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:12,400
Are you okay with that, Nuer?

144
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:15,120
Sure.

145
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,520
I don't have any problems with that.

146
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:19,040
I'm not the problematic one here.

147
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:20,520
But right now,

148
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:22,720
we should solve this problem first.

149
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:24,920
Dude, it's too hard.

150
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:44,920
I fixed it. Have a look.

151
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:49,160
Hey!

152
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:52,600
We've been trying to fix this problem for ages, but we couldn't do it.

153
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:53,680
How did you do it?

154
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:56,040
You're good at setting your hair and also fixing computers?

155
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,360
You're amazing!

156
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:12,880
The length of the front wheel...

157
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:16,680
630.

158
00:10:20,280 --> 00:10:23,200
Alright. Let's change this one here.

159
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:24,520
40 degrees, right?

160
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:33,880
Please forgive me, Kuea.

161
00:10:34,060 --> 00:10:35,880
It looks more symmetrical now.

162
00:10:39,820 --> 00:10:41,320
Let me go!

163
00:10:44,060 --> 00:10:45,300
Bring him this way!

164
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:52,240
What are you guys doing?

165
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:54,640
I'm so sorry, Kuea. But we have to do this.

166
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:56,180
We need to talk without Nuer following you around.

167
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:57,800
We can just talk in our group chat.

168
00:10:58,920 --> 00:10:59,920
Oh, right!

169
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:06,480
We can't! You might not believe us if you can't see our facial expressions.

170
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:08,400
We're really saying this from the bottom of our hearts.

171
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:11,520
I strictly uphold the five precepts.

172
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,200
You know it, right?

173
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:14,620
That I never lie.

174
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,520
Yeah!

175
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:19,680
I know.

176
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:22,520
What do you want to tell me?

177
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:28,280
No one thinks it's a good idea to let Nuer be in our group.

178
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:32,680
Why?

179
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:34,920
Syn.

180
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:37,080
You're acting weird these days.

181
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:38,440
That's because...

182
00:11:38,760 --> 00:11:41,680
Nuer is approaching you with bad intentions.

183
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:46,120
He knows that you already have a fiancé.

184
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:48,280
But he's still trying to flirt with you.

185
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:50,760
This is not something a good person does.

186
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:54,240
You're going too far.

187
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:56,320
Nuer hasn't even done anything yet.

188
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:59,120
I know Nuer's intention of approaching me.

189
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:01,680
But I don't care.

190
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:03,120
Okay?

191
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:04,440
Kuea.

192
00:12:05,040 --> 00:12:06,400
I agree with Syn.

193
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:08,800
I think Nuer is not a good person.

194
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:10,920
Listen to me, Kuea.

195
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:12,640
That day.

196
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:15,040
After our most entertaining football match.

197
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:18,320
You told us that you called off the engagement.

198
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:21,200
And I don't know what the situation with that is right now.

199
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:23,560
But after you left,

200
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:27,040
Nuer turned into a completely different person.

201
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,680
From white

202
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:31,160
to black.

203
00:12:32,040 --> 00:12:34,960
He made Syn so angry even his face turned red.

204
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:40,280
He's definitely got something up his sleeves!

205
00:12:41,520 --> 00:12:42,640
So what?

206
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:45,600
It's okay if he wants to flirt, isn't it?

207
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,720
I will call off my engagement with Hia Lian soon.

208
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:50,800
So you like Nuer?

209
00:12:58,440 --> 00:12:59,400
I don't.

210
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:02,480
Do I have to like everyone who approaches me?

211
00:13:05,040 --> 00:13:07,320
No one's ever tried approaching me before anyway.

212
00:13:18,920 --> 00:13:20,800
All throughout my life, there's only been Hia.

213
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:23,760
I've never cared about anyone else.

214
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:37,960
But right now.

215
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,800
I should start gaining experience.

216
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:44,200
But you should be careful, Kuea.

217
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:46,200
You're handsome and rich.

218
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:49,160
There will be people who approach you with questionable intentions.

219
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:50,720
That's fine!

220
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:53,240
I have you guys to protect me.

221
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,500
Especially you, Syn.

222
00:13:59,280 --> 00:14:00,920
Thank you so much.

223
00:14:01,880 --> 00:14:04,040
So when you told us you're going to be single soon...

224
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:05,800
Is that true?

225
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:07,880
Well...

226
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:17,240
Yeah.

227
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:23,120
Please forgive Kuea.

228
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:25,400
Everyone, put your hands together.

229
00:14:25,880 --> 00:14:28,240
Let's chant together, requesting for three refuges and five precepts.

230
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:33,520
"Mayam bhante."

231
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:36,080
"Visum visum."

232
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:38,720
"Rakkhanat thaya."

233
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:43,160
Wanna play football today?

234
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:44,880
Just a match!

235
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:46,360
You brought your clothes?

236
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:47,800
Of course!

237
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:50,320
Ton-Rak can wash, dry, and iron your clothes.

238
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:51,840
Wow. You're amazing.

239
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:53,020
Are you coming, Kuea?

240
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:55,200
Sure.

241
00:14:56,760 --> 00:14:57,520
Hey, guys!

242
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:00,600
Who's that guy?

243
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:02,040
He's wearing a suit on campus.

244
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:03,280
He looks like a mafia.

245
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:06,000
He's cool and handsome!

246
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:10,640
Shit!

247
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:14,360
What the hell?

248
00:15:15,240 --> 00:15:16,800
What's wrong with you?

249
00:15:18,520 --> 00:15:21,320
I haven't even called him yet. Why is he here?

250
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:23,200
What's wrong, Kuea?

251
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:29,160
That guy.

252
00:15:29,880 --> 00:15:30,840
That's Kilen Wang.

253
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:32,840
My fiancé.

254
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:34,040
I mean,

255
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:35,360
my ex-fiancé.

256
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:39,120
You're really something, Nu-Kuea.

257
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,360
Introduce us to him.

258
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:42,720
Why should I do that?

259
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:43,400
No way!

260
00:15:43,520 --> 00:15:44,480
Why not?

261
00:15:44,760 --> 00:15:46,240
Is he bothering you?

262
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:47,600
Do you want us to chase him away?

263
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,760
No, don't do that!

264
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:50,600
He's not bothering me.

265
00:15:50,640 --> 00:15:51,320
It's just...

266
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:53,640
I told him that I'm majoring in computer engineering.

267
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:57,080
If he finds out that I'm in automotive engineering,

268
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:58,960
he definitely wouldn't let me study here.

269
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:01,680
Well, I guess you have a point.

270
00:16:01,680 --> 00:16:03,520
But what's wrong with that?

271
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:06,240
Well...

272
00:16:06,520 --> 00:16:07,840
We're not neat and tidy.

273
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:11,200
So you're saying that we're lousy?!

274
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:12,520
That we're filthy?!

275
00:16:16,440 --> 00:16:18,200
That we're not like other normal human beings?!

276
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:21,400
No!

277
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:22,920
It's not like that.

278
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:27,520
Kuea.

279
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:29,240
How about this?

280
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:33,120
In order to prove that automotive engineer majors like us

